As Sandy wrote to Dr. Math
On 09/21/2004 at 15:11:20 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>Find 2 consecutive integers such that 4 times the samller is 9 more 
>than 3 times the larger.
>
>[Difficulty]
>I found what I think is the answer, but I only found 1.
>
>[Thoughts]
>4x = 9 + 3x
>4x - 3x = 9
>x = 9

Hi Sandy,

If you check your answer, you'll see that there's something wrong.

If the smaller one is 9, the larger one will be 10, and
4x9 = 36 is not 9 + 3x10 = 39.

The error is that if the smaller is x, then the larger one is x+1, so
your original equation should have been:

4x = 9 + 3(x+1).


